      "content": "Sure, I can help you with that. I'll write a function `extract_requirements` that parses the given text for mandatory requirements using basic keyword matching, considering this is a simple example. Here's a possible implementation:\n\n```python\ndef extract_requirements(text):\n    # List of keywords that typically appear in mandatory requirements\n    keywords = [\"must\", \"shall\", \"required\", \"must implement\", \"shall be notified\", \"required that\"]\n    \n    # Split the text into sentences\n    sentences = text.split('.')\n    \n    # Filter sentences containing mandatory requirement keywords\n    requirements = [sentence.strip() + '.' for sentence in sentences if any(keyword in sentence.lower() for keyword in keywords)]\n    \n    return requirements\n\n# Now, let's run the test script again with the updated extractor function\ntest_compliance_parser()\n```\n\nPlease keep in mind that this is a very basic approach and won't handle all cases in complex regulatory texts. For a production environment, consider using natural language processing techniques to better understand the context.",
